The paper deals with outlier detection in text data, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method involves matrix factorization, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of block coordinate descent, which is a common optimization technique in database systems (cs.DB).
